<br>
As she drew closer the woman reached down.  The distorted face smiled, and she spread her hand in the water, pressing it to Wrinn’s forehead… forcing her down.  Wrinn gasped in surprised, swallowing a mouthful of water, and feeling it burn into her lungs.  Suddenly, she panicked, aware of the air only inches above her head.  She clawed at the woman’s arm, trying to break free of her grasp.  She flailed with her left hand, upward, hoping to reach the woman’s face or throat.  Wishing she wasn’t naked… wishing she were armed.<br>
<br>
Her left arm met resistance, and she turned her head in surprise.  A Teir’dal male stared down at her, holding her left wrist in a grip of steel.  His fingers pressed into the bandages she wore wrapped around her left forearm to cover the spider web of scares that proclaimed her faith.  She stared up at him calmly, crouched, naked, on the floor at his feet within a large hall. She knew that she was somewhere in Neriak.  Around her, she sensed there were others… watching… ready.<br>
<br>
Without averting her eyes, she said calmly, “As the Father wills.”<br>
<br>
The Koada’dal’s eyes shot open, and she stared out of her window at the night sky.  She was filled with an immediate sense of urgency to return to Neriak without delay.  She rose and packed quickly, hurrying down the inn’s hallway.  The night quickly swallowed her as she moved through the streets of Freeport.<br>
