The missive fluttered unheeded to the floor from the slim pale fingers of her hand. &quot;So, they rebuild.. &quot; the words whispered softly as she turned from the fire and moved towards the center of the room. <br>
Dust kicked up as she walked. <br>
She had allowed no entrance into the inner sanctum, that had once been his office, since his disappearance so many moons back. As the months had progressed so had the chilling of her emotions. <br>
