A soft chanting cut through the silence of the room. Drowning out the chattering fire. Then a crack of thunder rent the stillness as a bright flash of light opened the portal. <br>
A tall stately woman stepped from the portal. Silver gaze cutting keenly through the darkness, as it returned to engulf the dying light of the portal. <br>
&quot;What is it now Chantress?&quot; The wizard hissed softly. She had no love for this creature. &quot;I've a task for you Sorceress.&quot; Was all Kat would say as she turned away from Grey. Oh she knew full well that Grey would gladely slice her wide open given the least provocation. She was however just as equally sure that at present she was something Grey needed. Once her usefullness to the Sorceress had passed however... <br>
<br>
Moving to the dust and paper strewn desk, Kat pulled a parchment from the mess and quickly wrote the instructions onto them as well as a brief message to the Thresher that would allow Grey entrance to the meeting. <br>
<br>
She turned and handed it to the Sorceress. &quot;Find out what you can and return to me. Inform Daiunus that though I will not at present leave the sanctity of my towers. I will instead send one in my steed should she prove of use to him.&quot;<br>
<br>
A delicate brow arched at the commands from the Chanteress. Grey rankled slightly at the orders, but nodded, her own curiousity peeked by the unfolding events. &quot;Very well.. &quot;<br>
<br>
She snatched the parchment from Kat and turned away, a brief wave of her hand brought light once more blindingly into the roomm She stepped through the summoned portal and vanished as it collapsed around her... <br>
